query_preview:
The bug is in the random-beans-validation package where randomizers are created with fixed seeds, causing them to generate identical values every time. Specifically, SizeAnnotationHandler creates new CharacterRandomizer instances with the same seed, and the string length randomizer doesn't use seeds at all. This affects all annotation handlers except those generating constant values. SizeAnnotationHandler CharacterRandomizer new CharacterRandomizer(seed)
